{
  "name": "@artale/pi-test-gen",
  "latest_version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "Auto-generate tests from code using AI",
  "readme": "# @artale/pi-test-gen\n\nAuto-generate tests from code using AI analysis.\n\n## Commands\n\n```\npi test-gen all       \u2192 Generate tests for all src files\npi test-gen file <path> \u2192 Generate tests for specific file\npi test-gen coverage   \u2192 Check test coverage\n```\n\n## Tools\n\n- `test_gen` - Generate tests for all source files\n- `test_gen_file` - Generate tests for a specific file\n- `test_gen_coverage` - Check test coverage\n\n## Install\n\n```bash\nnpm install -g @artale/pi-test-gen\n```\n\n## Features\n\n- Auto-detects test framework (vitest/jest)\n- Extracts functions, classes, exports\n- Generates skeleton tests with TODO comments\n- Supports JS, TS, JSX, TSX\n",
